deck: Pyg and Toad are back! This time, targeting victims in the fashion industry, culminating in a showdown with Batman and Katana on a yacht filled with the glitterati.
description: Professor Pyg and Mr. Toad are backand theyve set their sights on Gothams elite couture culture. Leaving clues that only Batman can decipher, they attack both a model and a clothing designer encasing them in deadly traps. Although Batman and Katana are able to save the day, they miss Pyg and Toads master plan: to destroy the yacht where the after-party for Gothams Fashion Week is being staged. Every fashion icon in the world will be there as well as Bruce Wayne!
name: Instinct

deck: Buffy's mother has a new boyfriend, and he really creeps Buffy out.
description: Buffy walks into the kitchen and finds her mom kissing a strange man. He learns that this is her mother's new boyfriend, Ted. Buffy is "O.K." with him at first, but that soon turns to suspicion as he begins behaving strangely, and ultimately threatens her.
name: Ted

deck: Buffy and her friends are given eggs in health class. That turn out to be prehistoric parasites that have taken over the school.
description:
In a sex ed class, Buffy and friends are given eggs to take care of as an exercise in responsibility. Meanwhile a couple of Old West cowboy vampires show up in Sunnydale, and witness Buffy and Angel making out.

Buffy is caught sneaking out and grounded by her mother. Confined to her room she witnesses her egg hatch an arthropod type creature. Soon she and Xander (who boiled his egg) learn that all the others have been taken over by the creatures hatched from their own eggs.
name: Bad Eggs

deck: Buffy and Angel must stop Spike and Drusilla from raising The Judge.
description:
Spike and Drusilla plan to raise "The Judge", an unkillable demon whose living dismembered parts have been scattered across the globe.

Meanwhile, it's Buffy's 17th birthday, and she and Angel get serious about their relationship.
name: Surprise

deck: After spending the night with Buffy, Angel's soul is removed, and he becomes Angelus the evil vampire once again. He joins up with Spike and Drusilla to bring The Judge back to power and destroy the earth.
description:
Immediately following the events of the previous episode, "Surprise", the Scooby Gang is in a near panic when neither Buffy nor Angel turns up the day after going looking for The Judge.

Meanwhile, Buffy and Angel have slept together for the first time, which breaks the curse on Angel, removing his soul. He's soon up to his old tricks with his old friends Spike and Drusilla, first of which involves breaking Buffy's heart.

Willow is crushed when she catches Xander making out with Cordelia in the library stacks.

Jenny Calendar finally reveals her mission to Buffy and Giles.

Xander comes up with a plan to defeat The Judge.
name: Innocence

deck: Dr. McNamara hires a gang, called the Vandals, to cause havok in Old Detroit. Only RocoCop can stop this menace, otherwise Dr. McNamara gets to put his ED-260 on the streets of Old Detroit.
name: Crime Wave

description: Seventy years after the end of the original series, the Order of the White Lotus discovers the new Avatar, Korra, in the Southern Water Tribe. By the age of 17, Korra has mastered all the elements except air. Master Tenzin, Katara's and Aang's son, and the only airbending master, wants to postpone Korra's airbending training in order to take care of matters in Republic City, but Korra convinces him to train her. After a clash with local triads, she is arrested by Lin Beifong, head of Republic City's metalbending police force and the daughter of Toph. Meanwhile, antagonist 'Amon' is identified as the leader of the anti-bender "Equalist" movement.
name: Welcome to Republic City

description:
Korra learns about the epic and mythic origins of the first Avatar.

While being healed by the Fire Sages, Korra explores her past lives and meets Wan, the first Avatar, who lived 10,000 years ago. Living in a time where humans lived on the shells of lion turtles to protect themselves from the spirits, Wan and his friends live in poverty and hunger. One day, Wan steals the power of firebending, but is banished for it after stealing food from the local tyrant to feed his friends. After learning to survive in the treacherous jungles, Wan befriends the spirits living there. Two years later, when Wan begins traveling the mainland, he encounters two powerful spirits battling each other. After being tricked by one of the spirits, Wan separates the two. While one spirit escapes, the other spirit, Raava, explains that she is the spirit of light and peace and that the spirit Wan had freed is Vaatu, the spirit of darkness and chaos. By freeing Vaatu, Wan has unwittingly let destruction and chaos into the world.
name: Beginnings, Part 1

deck: In the wake of Unicron's defeat, the battered Decepticons struggle to survive, and the Autobots enjoy a period of peace and celebration. But peace never lasts...
description: One year after the events of The Transformers: The Movie, the leaderless Decepticons have set up base on the planet Charr, their Energon stores depleted and their ambition for conquest lost. Disgusted by this, Cyclonus sets out to search for the missing Galvatron. On a faraway planet Rodimus Prime officiates the First Galactic Olympics, but chaos erupts when the Olympic Torch explodes in an act of sabotage and Kup, Ultra Magnus, and Spike are kidnapped amidst the commotion. Following a lead on Earth, Blaster and Outback discover the location of Charr, allowing Rodimus and Grimlock to head there to look for their missing comrades.
name: Five Faces of Darkness, Part 1

deck: Dee Dee tampers with Dexter's machine./A monster couldn't need loud noise./Dexter creates a robot version of his mother.
name: Deedeemensional/Magmanamus/Maternal Combat

deck: As a near death experience on Chaar allows Rodimus Prime to discover who kidnapped the Autobots, Cyclonus and Scourge head to rescue Galvatron...only to find that something is very wrong with their leader.
description: Rodimus and Grimlock are overwhelmed by Decepitcon forces, but a strange spaceship rescues them from captivity on Charr. Cyclonus, Scourge and the Sweeps locate Galvatron, asking him to lead the Decepticons once more, but find their former leader filled with an unstable rage. On Quintessa, Kup, Ultra Magnus, and Spike are interrogated by the maniacal Quintessons and found guilty for the unlawful inhabitation of planet Cybertron. Traveling into the Matrix of Leadership, Rodimus Prime sees a vision of the Quintessons and, returning from his vision quest, leads a rescue for to Quintessa.
name: Five Faces of Darkness, Part 2

deck: Desperate to destroy the Autobots, the Quintessons make a deal with the Decepticons.
description: Escaping Quintessa, Rodimus and his allies crash-land and become stuck on Goo 8739B, a planetoid made up of a strange, viscous substance. Galvatron returns to the Solar System and intercepts a shuttle piloted by Blurr and Wheelie, who have been charged with delivering Metroplex's Transformation Cog to Autobot City on Earth. Blurr and Wheelie crash on Io, one of Jupiter's larger moons. Back on CHarr, the Quintessons arrive and make the languishing Decepitcons an offer they can't refuse: unlimited Energon for the destruction of the Autobots!
name: Five Faces of Darkness, Part 3

deck: Dexter uses a clone machine so he won't get bothered by Dee Dee and her friends./Barbequor prepares to eat Earth./Dexter and Dee Dee use a remote to change forms.
name: Double Trouble/Barbequor/Changes

deck: Seeking answers about their mysterious new foes, Rodimus Prime takes a journey through the Matrix to learn the truth about the Quintessons... and the origins of the Transformers.
description: Galvatron arrives on Goo just in time to bring the Quintesson-powered Decepticons back to his side and immediately threatens to kill the nearby Quintessons for stealing his troops. The Quintessons calm the Decepticon leader with the promise of the Decepitcon Matrix of Leadership, and the two teams call a truce. In a surprise move, Wreck-Gar attempts to rescur the Goo-bound AUtobots. Seeking answers to the mysterious of the Quintessons, Rodimus Prime takes a dangerous journey into the Matrix once again and learns the true origins of the Transformers!
name: Five Faces of Darkness, Part 4

deck: Samurai Jack is encountered by Aku's most powerful minion, Demongo.
name: Jack Vs Demongo, The Soul Collector

deck: With Earth and Cybertron under joint Decepticon-Quintesson assault, the Autobots raise a last stand against their old enemies... and the race which created them.
description: On Earth, a mammoth new Decepticon named Trypticon destroys the Ark and heads toward Autobot City. On Cybertron, a Decepticon armada attack while the Autobots' planetary defenses are down. SkyLynx and the Predacons each head to Io to secure the wayward Transformation Cog - but the Quintessons have an ace up their sleeve, planning a betrayal of Galvatron and the immediate destruction of all Transformer live on Cybertron.
name: Five Faces of Darkness, Part 5

deck: The Doctor, Ian, Susan and Barbara go visit Marco Polo.
description:
***All of these Episodes are missing***

Written by: John Lucarotti

Directed by: Waris Hussein (Episodes 1-3, 5-7), John Crockett (Episode 4)

Episode 1: Roof of the World

Episode 2: The Singing Sands

Episode 3: Five Hundred Eye

Episode 4: Wall of Lies

Episode 5: Rider of Shang-Tu

Episode 6: Might Kublai Khan

Episode 7: Assassin at Perking

Synopsis:

Arriving in Central Asia in 1289, the Doctor and his companions join the caravan of the famous Venetian explorer Marco Polo as it makes its way from the snowy heights of the Pamir Plateau, across the treacherous Gobi Desert and through the heart of imperial Cathay.

Having witnessed many incredible sights and survived a variety of dangers, they arrive at the mighty Kublai Khan's Summer Palace in Shang-tu, where the Doctor strikes up an extraordinary friendship with the now-aged ruler.

They move on at last to the even more sumptuous Imperial Palace in Peking, where the travellers save the Khan from an assassination attempt by the Mongol warlord Tegana - supposedly on a peace mission - before departing once more in the TARDIS.
name: Marco Polo

deck: Can the Doctor find all the keys to Marinus?
description:
Written by: Terry Nation

Directed by: John Gorrie

Episode 1: The Sea of Death

Episode 2: The Velvet of Web

Episode 3: The Screaming Jungle

Episode 4: The Snows of Terror

Episode 5: Sentence of Death

Episode 6: The Key of Marinus

The TARDIS arrives on the planet Marinus on an island of glass surrounded by a sea of acid. The travellers are forced by the elderlyArbitan to retrieve four of the five operating keys to a machine called the Conscience of Marinus, of which he is the keeper. These have been hidden in different locations around the planet to prevent them falling into the hands of the evil Yartek and hisVoord warriors, who plan to seize the machine and use its originally benevolent mind-influencing power for their own sinister purposes.
name: The Keys of Marinus
